turns and descends ..."

40
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:24,825
The ten graves of Malebolge.

41
00:36:25,084 --> 00:36:30,963
First circle
Ruffians, punished by demons, are whipped.
Venedico Caccianimico.

42
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:24,964
Second circle
Flatterers and loose women are immersed in manure. Alessio Interminei and Thais.
"... That dirty and disheveled slave,
that there scratches with her nails, and now she lies there.  Thais is the prostitute"

43
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:19,357
Third Circle
The greedies are buried upside down, with the soles of their feet on fire.
Pope Nicholas III.
Dante rages against the Papacy.

44
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:51,990
Fourth Circle
Soothsayers, neck and face twisted, walking backwards.

45
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:04,043
Fifth Circle
The angry, immersed in boiling pitch, are guarded by demons.

46
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:54,634
Malacoda chooses the ten demon devils to escort the poets.

47
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:05,528
Ciampolo falls into the power of the demons and, deceiving them, escapes.
Two of them are fighting.

48
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:08,283
Demons chasing the poets.

49
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:35,240
Sixth Circle.
Hypocrites, walking under heavy blankets of lead.

50
00:43:35,480 --> 00:43:42,937
Caiaphas, crucified on the floor and trampled by anyone who passes.

51
00:46:50,800 --> 00:47:01,026
Seventh Circle
Thieves, bitten horribly by snakes.
Vanni Fucci predicted to Dante the defeat of the Whites.

52
00:48:08,377 --> 00:48:15,522
Thieves of public money, men converted into snakes and vice versa.

53
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:11,915
Eighth Circle
Fraudulent counselors, each wrapped in a flame.
"Odysseus and Diomedes are in there, tortured..."

54
00:49:30,240 --> 00:49:36,229
Ninth Circle
Those who sow discord and schisms, mutilated by demons.

55
00:49:36,229 --> 00:49:45,945
Muhammad with his torn chest.
Born Bertram head disembodied.
"Gripping the head hair cut short,
like a lantern carrying it in your hand."

56
00:51:03,280 --> 00:51:07,389
Tenth Circle
Counterfeiters, converted to lepers, crazy and sick.

57
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:42,510
Nembrot, Efialte, Antaeus: The Giants

58
00:53:09,840 --> 00:53:15,353
Anteo holds the poets in his hands. 
"... Slightly in the background, ...
... He led us."

59
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:24,375
Traitors, submerged in the frozen lake of Cocytus.

60
00:53:55,840 --> 00:54:02,987
The Antenora.
The traitors of the motherland. 

61
00:54:51,720 --> 00:54:59,423
Count Ugolino, gnawing on the skull of Archbishop Ruggeri.
"From the fierce meal he lifted his mouth."

62
00:56:18,440 --> 00:56:35,400
Count Ugolino recounts the story of his death and his sons, in the Tower of Pisa.
"... And it was me, and blind, groping about for them, two days I called to them, but they were dead.  After the pain followed more fasting."

63
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:37,637
The Tolomea. Friends, traitors. Friar Alberigo prays to Dante to remove the ice from their eyes.

64
01:02:21,760 --> 01:02:27,124
Judea
The traitors of their benefactors.
Lucifer.

65
01:03:06,080 --> 01:03:09,032
The underground way.

66
